message.content:
1. The mean glycemic level during the 4-h infusion without quinine was 83 ± 5 mg/dl using saline solute.
2. The mean glycemic level during the 4-h infusion with quinine was 74 ± 5 mg/dl using saline solute.
3. The difference in mean glycemic levels with and without quinine using saline solute was statistically significant (p < 0.001).
4. The mean glycemic level during the 4-h infusion without quinine was 92 ± 7 mg/dl when associated with the glucose solute.
5. The mean glycemic level during the 4-h infusion with quinine was 82 ± 5 mg/dl when associated with the glucose solute.
6. The difference in mean glycemic levels with and without quinine when associated with the glucose solute was statistically significant (p < 0.001).
